{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When writing a function, method, or other API that might fail, you use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"throws"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"keyword on the declaration to indicate that the API call can throw an error. However,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"you can’t use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"throws","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" keyword to model APIs that return asynchronously. Instead,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"use the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" enumeration to capture information about whether an asychronous"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call succeeds or fails, and use the associated values for the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/success(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/failure(_:)"},{"text":" cases to carry information about the result of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"call.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Return Result Instances Asynchronously","level":3,"anchor":"Return-Result-Instances-Asynchronously"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example models an asynchronous source of random numbers. The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fetchRemoteRandomNumber(completion:)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"method returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"Void","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" synchronously, and asynchronously calls a completion handler","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result<Int, EntropyError>"},{"type":"text","text":" instance that contains either a random result"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or information about the failure.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let queue = DispatchQueue(label: \"com.example.queue\")","","enum EntropyError: Error {","    case entropyDepleted","}","","struct AsyncRandomGenerator {","    static let entropyLimit = 5","    var count = 0","","    mutating func fetchRemoteRandomNumber(","        completion: @escaping (Result<Int, EntropyError>) -> Void","    ) {","        let result: Result<Int, EntropyError>","        if count < AsyncRandomGenerator.entropyLimit {","            \/\/ Produce numbers until reaching the entropy limit.","            result = .success(Int.random(in: 1...100))","        } else {","            \/\/ Supply a failure reason when the caller hits the limit.","            result = .failure(.entropyDepleted)","        }","","        count += 1","","        \/\/ Delay to simulate an asynchronous source of entropy.","        queue.asyncAfter(deadline: .now() + 2) {","            completion(result)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Users of your remote random number generator can decide how to handle both the success","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and failure cases:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["var generator = AsyncRandomGenerator()","","\/\/ Request one more number than the limit to trigger a failure.","(0..<AsyncRandomGenerator.entropyLimit + 1).forEach { _ in","    generator.fetchRemoteRandomNumber { result in","        switch result {","        case .success(let number):","            print(number)","        case .failure(let error):","            print(\"Source of randomness failed: \\(error)\")","        }","    }","}","","print(\"Waiting on some numbers.\")","","dispatchMain()","\/* Prints:","success(29)","success(46)","success(85)","success(39)","success(84)","Source of randomness failed: entropyDepleted","*\/"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/writing-failable-asynchronous-apis"},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Swift"}],"role":"article","title":"Writing Failable Asynchronous APIs"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Vend results as part of an API when you can’t return errors synchronously.","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Representing a Result","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/success(_:)","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/failure(_:)"],"anchor":"Representing-a-Result"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/numbers-and-basic-values","doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result"]]},"references":{"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Result":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Result"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/result","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Result"}],"type":"topic","title":"Result","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A value that represents either a success or a failure, including an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"associated value in each case."}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/numbers-and-basic-values":{"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/numbers-and-basic-values","abstract":[{"text":"Model data with numbers, Boolean values, and other fundamental types.","type":"text"}],"title":"Numbers and Basic Values","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/numbers-and-basic-values","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup"},"Swift-PageImage-card.png":{"type":"image","alt":"An orange Swift logo on a gradient background.","identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","variants":[{"traits":["2x","light"],"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card@2x.png"},{"traits":["2x","dark"],"url":"\/images\/com.apple.Swift\/Swift-PageImage-card~dark@2x.png"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift":{"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift","type":"topic","title":"Swift","images":[{"identifier":"Swift-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build apps using a powerful open language."}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Result/failure(_:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"failure","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Failure","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s6ResultOsRi_zRi0_zrlE7Failureq_mfp"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/result\/failure(_:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/failure(_:)","title":"Result.failure(_:)","abstract":[{"text":"A failure, storing a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value.","type":"text"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/swift-standard-library":{"role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/swift\/swift-standard-library","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/swift-standard-library","type":"topic","title":"Swift Standard Library","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Solve complex problems and write high-performance, readable code.","type":"text"}]},"doc://com.apple.Swift/documentation/Swift/Result/success(_:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"success","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s6ResultOsRi_zRi0_zrlE7Successxmfp","text":"Success"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swift\/result\/success(_:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.apple.Swift\/documentation\/Swift\/Result\/success(_:)","title":"Result.success(_:)","abstract":[{"text":"A success, storing a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Success","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" value."}]}}}